Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.62,0:00:28.67,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki Hotaro-{\i1}dono{\i0},
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.83,0:00:28.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Oreki Hotaro-{\i1}dono{\i0},
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.25,0:00:35.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Greetings. I am currently in Varanasi. Sorry for\Nbeing so late but congratulations on passing.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.18,0:00:38.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You ended up going to\NKamiyama High School, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.72,0:00:40.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that you've safely become\Na high school student,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.93,0:00:43.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have some sisterly advice for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.60,0:00:46.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Join the Classic Lit Club.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.44,0:00:51.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a time-honored club.\NIt's also the club that I was in.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.99,0:00:57.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,From what I've heard, the club\Ncurrently has zero members.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.03,0:00:59.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Without any new members this year,\Nthe club will be done away with.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.37,0:01:03.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As one of the club's old girls,\NI couldn't bear for that to happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.12,0:01:06.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hotaro,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.96,0:01:10.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,preserve the Classic Lit Club,\Nthe site of your sister's adolescence.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.42,0:01:12.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you just put your name in.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.96,0:01:15.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, you don't have anything\Nelse you want to do, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.05,0:01:19.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sincerely, Oreki Tomoe."
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.97,0:01:25.35,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I scowled at the wind blowing\Nat my window of boredom{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.35,0:01:33.44,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}so I could turn away\Nthe awkwardness I was feeling{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.69,0:01:41.58,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Hyouka
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.58,0:01:47.00,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I nod noncommittally at today\Nas I hold it in my hand{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.00,0:01:52.38,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}projecting myself a little exaggeratedly{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.38,0:01:57.88,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I get the feeling that\Nsomething is about to change{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.88,0:02:02.97,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's all because of you\Ncalling out to my heart{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.43,0:02:09.85,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Peeking up at cloudy skies,\NI sense what's coming{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.85,0:02:17.86,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Let's reach out our hands\Nwith courage stronger than ever{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.24,0:02:22.83,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Light and shadow are both still far off{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.83,0:02:29.08,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}but even so, we want to know\Nthe reason for this kindness{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.08,0:02:36.51,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Let's go look now, beyond the brilliance\Nthat goes by nobody's name{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.51,0:02:49.06,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}before it all becomes a thing of the past{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.64,0:02:51.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,1, 2, 3, 4!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.90,0:02:54.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lt's been a month since the\NClassic Lit Club made its comeback.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.48,0:02:56.94,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,The Prestigious Classic Lit Club's Activities
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.98,0:03:00.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Earth\NScience prep room has become more familiar than I expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.57,0:02:57.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,... Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.94,0:02:59.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,... Yo.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.11,0:03:04.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I feel bored after school,\Nthat's where I go.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.70,0:03:07.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Help yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.62,0:03:08.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.41,0:03:12.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Some snacks from home.\NHelp yourself to anything you like.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.58,0:03:14.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.42,0:03:17.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not as though I ever\Ndisliked being with anyone,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.46,0:03:20.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so long as it didn't wear me out.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.94,0:03:41.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is fruitless.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.57,0:03:44.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You mean planting two crops a year?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.41,0:03:46.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, that's double-cropping.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.29,0:03:50.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Were you trying to make a joke?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.33,0:03:51.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.21,0:03:53.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I don't mean that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.37,0:03:54.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is fruitless?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.54,0:03:56.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, fruitless.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.46,0:03:56.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.13,0:04:03.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our whole afterschool time! Our days\Nbeing spent aimlessly is not productive!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.59,0:04:05.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't agree more.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.30,0:04:09.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, is there something you're\Nhoping to get out of the Classic Lit Club?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.60,0:04:10.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, there is.\NOh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.48,0:04:13.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But that is a personal matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.81,0:04:15.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She said that before, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.73,0:04:18.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right now, I'm talking about\Nthe Classic Lit Club.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.57,0:04:21.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As a club, we should have\Nsome club activities.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.99,0:04:22.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no point.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.78,0:04:28.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, there is. We'll submit an anthology\Nto the culture festival in October.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.78,0:04:29.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anthology?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.83,0:04:30.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.83,0:04:32.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's not. It's too much work.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.91,0:04:35.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, there has to be an anthology!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.62,0:04:37.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you want to get involved\Nwith the culture festival,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.84,0:04:41.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,there are other ways to do it.\NLike a refreshment stand.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.26,0:04:45.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kami High's culture festivals have\Ntraditionally prohibited refreshment stands.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.68,0:04:48.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, we'll get a budget\Nprovided for the anthology,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.64,0:04:51.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and our advising teacher\Nhas asked us to do one, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.97,0:04:55.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Also, an anthology has been\Na tradition for over 40 years,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.85,0:04:57.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and they don't want to break it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.77,0:05:00.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, why didn't you say so sooner?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.40,0:05:02.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, we'll do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.40,0:05:03.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.40,0:05:07.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So then, what is this anthology\Nsupposed to contain?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.28,0:05:09.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.03,0:05:10.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.33,0:05:13.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, I thought we could\Nlook into that now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.29,0:05:17.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyhow, if there are any back-number\Nissues, I thought we could start there.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.17,0:05:19.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's look for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.10,0:05:30.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They aren't here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.39,0:05:35.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, maybe they're in\Nthe library. Let's go see.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.23,0:05:42.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing?\NOreki-{\i1}san{\i0}, you're going, too. Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.91,0:05:51.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm in no mood for this.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.83,0:05:55.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's Friday, so the person\Non library duty is probably...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.00,0:05:56.46,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Library
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.79,0:06:00.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, if it isn't Oreki. Long time\Nno see. I haven't missed you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.29,0:06:03.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yo, Ibara. I came to see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.92,0:06:07.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is educational sacred ground.\NIt's not really your bag, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.18,0:06:12.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So then, you're saying that it\N{\i1}is {\i0}yours? How laudable of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.10,0:06:17.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're as awful as ever. If you're\Nhere to crack wise, go away.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.14,0:06:17.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.35,0:06:20.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Hotaro! Fancy running into you here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.02,0:06:23.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see you two are as chummy as ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.23,0:06:25.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What else would you expect from\NKaburaya Middle School's "Best Couple"?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.73,0:06:26.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.90,0:06:30.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd rather be with a slug\Nthan {\i1}this {\i0}dismal downer.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.32,0:06:31.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Slug...?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.62,0:06:34.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look here, Fuku-{\i1}chan{\i0}, you've got\Nsome nerve knowing how I feel
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.83,0:06:36.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and still making a joke like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.54,0:06:39.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, sorry, Mayaka. Did I offend you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.12,0:06:43.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There you go again, trying to\Nchange the subject by joking.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.75,0:06:46.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously, cut it out, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.38,0:06:49.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How do those two know each other?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.93,0:06:53.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's had a crush on Satoshi\Nsince middle school.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.05,0:06:54.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.72,0:06:55.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ahem...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.10,0:06:58.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chitanda-{\i1}san{\i0}, this is Ibara Mayaka.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.85,0:07:01.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She went to Kaburaya\NMiddle School, same as us.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.31,0:07:02.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a pleasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.73,0:07:05.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mayaka, this is Chitanda Eru-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.61,0:07:08.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's the president of the\NClassic Lit Club, which I recently joined.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.28,0:07:11.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The pleasure is all mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.70,0:07:14.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So anyway, what brings\Nthe both of you here?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.12,0:07:18.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right. Um, Ibara-{\i1}san{\i0},\Nthere's something I'd like to ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.91,0:07:19.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.87,0:07:24.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you keep any club anthologies here?\NFrom the Classic Lit Club?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.88,0:07:26.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Classic Lit Club...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.63,0:07:28.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think we do.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.84,0:07:30.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If they're not out here,\Nmaybe they're in the back stacks.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.01,0:07:32.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.72,0:07:34.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you need the anthologies?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.35,0:07:37.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We've decided to make an\Nanthology for the culture festival,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.31,0:07:40.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so I thought we'd have a look at\Nthe previous anthologies first.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.06,0:07:42.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah? We're presenting it at Kanyasai?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.65,0:07:44.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm surprised Hotaro went along with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.61,0:07:47.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was largely ex-post-facto approval.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.73,0:07:48.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Kanyasai"?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.23,0:07:52.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've never heard of it? It's an abbreviation\Nfor "Kamiyama High School Culture Festival."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.66,0:07:55.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not another one of your\Nthought-up abbreviations, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.57,0:07:59.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's for real! All the guys in\Nthe Handicrafts Club call it "Kanyasai."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.79,0:08:00.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How about you, Mayaka?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.75,0:08:03.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They call it "Kanyasai"\Nin the Manga Club, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.46,0:08:06.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Kanya"? How do they write that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.17,0:08:11.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know. I {\i1}have {\i0}asked\Naround about it, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.05,0:08:13.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Though it probably started as\NKamiyama High School {\i1}Bunkasai{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.97,0:08:16.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,being shortened to "Kamiyama-{\i1}sai{\i0},"\Nthen "Kanyama-{\i1}sai{\i0},"
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.64,0:08:19.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and finally "Kanyasai,"\Nor at least that's what I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.35,0:08:20.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So anyway, Chitanda-{\i1}san{\i0},
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.89,0:08:24.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,there may be anthologies\Nif we check in the back stacks,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.19,0:08:27.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but the librarian is out\Nat a meeting at the moment,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.06,0:08:28.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so we can't get in there right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.98,0:08:32.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think she'll be back in another\N30 minutes or so, though. Want to wait?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.32,0:08:34.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What should we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.45,0:08:35.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.57,0:08:38.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You could always leave, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.12,0:08:39.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.00,0:08:42.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, Hotaro!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.20,0:08:45.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mayaka, can I tell these two\Nthe story you told me earlier?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.92,0:08:46.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.79,0:08:54.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm, okay. Oreki, feel like putting\Nyour brain to work for a change?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.84,0:08:55.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.22,0:08:56.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What story is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.34,0:08:59.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The story of the Most Favored\NBook of Disfavor.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.35,0:09:00.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Most Favored Book of Disfavor?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.14,0:09:03.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is quite the peculiar tale.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.35,0:09:05.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how I look at it,\Nit doesn't add up.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.77,0:09:07.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It has Mayaka and I both\Njust about baffled.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.94,0:09:10.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please, tell us about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.53,0:09:14.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I come here every Friday after school,\Nbecause I'm on duty, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.20,0:09:18.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And every week, the same\Nbook gets returned.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.03,0:09:22.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Today marks the fifth week in a row.\NThat by itself is unusual, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.29,0:09:24.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is that book.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.50,0:09:26.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, what a pretty book.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.79,0:09:28.17,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Kamiyama High School's 50-Year Progress
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.79,0:09:28.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's huge.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.63,0:09:30.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Would you mind if I looked inside?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.42,0:09:31.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.59,0:09:36.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}, here, look.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.51,0:09:42.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a normal school history, huh? Hmm...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.56,0:09:46.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like it would be a lot\Nof work to read through this.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.19,0:09:52.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmph. It's not so unusual that\Nsomeone would check this out every week.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.27,0:09:55.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've never borrowed a book\Nfrom here, have you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.90,0:09:59.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The checkout period\Nat this library is two weeks.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.20,0:10:01.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So there's no need to borrow it every week.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.83,0:10:05.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Despite which, this book is\Nalso returned each week.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.45,0:10:07.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know who it was that borrowed it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.67,0:10:08.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.62,0:10:10.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The checkout list is inside it,\Nso take a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.38,0:10:15.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}, please look at this!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.63,0:10:18.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Each week, a different person checks it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.63,0:10:20.89,OS,,0000,0000,0000,,Suzuki Konoe\NShima Saor\NYamaguchi Ryoko\NSawakiguchi Misaki\NKyoko Machida
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.13,0:10:20.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's more, they all return it on the very same day.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.89,0:10:32.27,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Suzuki Konoe
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.30,0:10:25.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. It gets\Nchecked out and returned the same day,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.22,0:10:28.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,for five weeks in a row now.\NI even know the times,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.27,0:10:32.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and all five of them check it out\Nat lunch, and return it after school.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.77,0:10:35.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How about it? Got you curious, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.90,0:10:36.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.61,0:10:39.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am curious!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.37,0:10:47.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's think about this\Nfor a bit, Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.08,0:10:49.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it, Satoshi!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.37,0:10:51.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See? What do you think? Interesting, right? You\Nknew this would happen when you stopped me, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.67,0:10:55.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}, you did such a nice\Njob of solving that lock matter,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.55,0:10:57.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and that secret club business, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.47,0:11:00.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.30,0:11:03.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It involves a deeply provocative\Nfacet to Hotaro here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.22,0:11:04.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Knock that off. You make it sound sordid.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.39,0:11:07.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In any event, it inspires curiosity.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.64,0:11:09.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It does not.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.48,0:11:11.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It does so!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.06,0:11:12.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It does not!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.48,0:11:13.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.27,0:11:16.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Be quiet. You, too, Chitanda-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.94,0:11:18.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.94,0:11:19.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.36,0:11:24.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was careless.\NAny further refusals or prevarication
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.16,0:11:26.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,will be an inefficient use of energy now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.33,0:11:27.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As such...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.04,0:11:32.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, all right. I guess\NI'll think about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.50,0:11:34.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.46,0:11:41.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fuku-{\i1}chan{\i0}, was Oreki ever smart?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.76,0:11:45.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not so much. But when it comes\Nto useless stuff like this,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.10,0:11:46.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he can sometimes be helpful.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.93,0:11:49.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're not holding anything back, are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.02,0:11:52.02,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Rikka {\i0}('Dawn of Summer')\NWhen we hail the rise of summer
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.35,0:11:52.02,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Hyouka
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.06,0:11:56.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For five weeks straight, different people\Nhave borrowed this book,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.40,0:11:57.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and then returned it the same day.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.57,0:12:01.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It would be easy to insist\Nthat it was a coincidence,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.28,0:12:02.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but Chitanda probably\Nwouldn't be convinced.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.61,0:12:05.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The truth isn't what's important here;
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.91,0:12:07.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it's being able to convince Chitanda.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.54,0:12:09.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now then...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.91,0:12:12.58,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Lunch Break
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.91,0:12:12.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,borrowing the book at\Nlunch and returning it after school
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.58,0:12:14.17,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,After School
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.58,0:12:15.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,doesn't leave\Nvery much time for reading it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.17,0:12:15.92,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Lunch Break + Class Break + Class Break = 65 minutes:\NInsufficient
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.92,0:12:17.25,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,School\NHome
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.92,0:12:17.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If they're not taking it home with them,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.25,0:12:18.88,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,No
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.88,0:12:20.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,they can just read it in the\Nlibrary without borrowing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.55,0:12:25.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Conclusion: This book is not being\Nused to fulfill a literary purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.89,0:12:27.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which would mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.93,0:12:31.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you were to use the book for something\Nother than reading, how would you use it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.81,0:12:34.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you stack a few of them up,\Nit might make a good pillow.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.65,0:12:36.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you put it on your arm,\Nit would serve as a shield.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.86,0:12:38.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Think about this more seriously.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.69,0:12:43.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's right. There must be some way\Nthat this book in particular is being used.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.11,0:12:45.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, Chitanda-{\i1}san{\i0}, what do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.53,0:12:47.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.70,0:12:49.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you make a stack of them,\Nthey could serve as pickle press.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.12,0:12:52.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to stop asking you guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.91,0:12:55.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is Chitanda really an honor student?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.54,0:12:58.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She strikes me as being just a doofus.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.55,0:13:01.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's look at this a different way.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.46,0:13:05.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What does it mean that each week,\Na different person is borrowing it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.76,0:13:07.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Looking at the names,\Nthey're all girls, aren't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.72,0:13:09.35,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,One\NTwo
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.60,0:13:10.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are two ways to think about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.06,0:13:16.98,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Friday
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.06,0:13:13.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The girls have nothing in common,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.10,0:13:16.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but the book comes into\Nvogue every Friday afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.98,0:13:20.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or, the girls use the book as a group,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.73,0:13:21.53,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Friday
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.36,0:13:21.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and they each take turns
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.53,0:13:23.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,borrowing the book for them to use.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.69,0:13:23.74,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,One\NNon-group\NTwo\NGroup
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.74,0:13:25.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In vogue, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.74,0:13:26.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For fortunetelling, maybe?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.66,0:13:32.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, like this! "Your lucky item\Nthis week is the school history!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.24,0:13:36.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you borrow it Friday afternoon,\Nand return it that same day,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.25,0:13:39.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you will get on well with\Nyour boyfriend," maybe?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.04,0:13:42.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's ridiculous.\NBesides, it's five weeks in a row.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.46,0:13:43.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was just thinking out loud.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.26,0:13:46.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Their common points are\Nthat they're all girls,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.43,0:13:48.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and they're all 2nd-years,\Nbut in different classes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.64,0:13:52.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if there might be some\Nreason why they're all girls.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.39,0:13:56.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's really no telling. If you pick\Nfive random people out of the school,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.69,0:13:59.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,there's a fair possibility that\Nthey would all be girls.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.65,0:14:03.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's also not unusual for members\Nof the same sex to group together.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.44,0:14:05.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What if it were some kind of signal?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.86,0:14:09.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like if the book is returned\Nface-up, it means "yea,"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.16,0:14:10.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and face-down means "nay."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.82,0:14:14.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm... I don't think you could\Nsignal by which side was up.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.54,0:14:17.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.00,0:14:18.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fair point.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.00,0:14:20.50,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Returns Corner
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.50,0:14:20.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't tell which\Nof those face up or down, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.96,0:14:22.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.17,0:14:26.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, no matter how hard Oreki\Nracks his brain, that's what you'll get.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.26,0:14:30.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After all, Fuku-{\i1}chan {\i0}and I thought\Nas hard as we could about this...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.59,0:14:32.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.72,0:14:34.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It has an odor about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.39,0:14:35.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It does?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.02,0:14:39.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't smell anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.73,0:14:40.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'm sure of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.94,0:14:44.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a kind of acrid odor.\NLike paint thinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.15,0:14:46.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no doubt about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.11,0:14:48.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is she a dog?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.70,0:14:53.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, well, if Chitanda-{\i1}san {\i0}insists\Nshe smells it, she can't be wrong, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.28,0:14:55.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which would mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.21,0:15:01.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hotaro, you've got that look\Nlike you've figured something out.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.08,0:15:02.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.38,0:15:04.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, maybe. I can't be positive, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.21,0:15:07.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chitanda, are you up for a little exercise?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.88,0:15:09.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's somewhere I'd like you to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.88,0:15:10.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.30,0:15:15.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Er, no, I'm not going, just you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.10,0:15:16.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just me? How come?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.31,0:15:19.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, um...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.48,0:15:21.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're right, Chitanda-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.77,0:15:24.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You shouldn't let yourself\Nbe used by Hotaro!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.69,0:15:27.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hotaro is most helpful when\Nyou make use of {\i1}him{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.82,0:15:29.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a hell of a way to talk about me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.45,0:15:33.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no, I just thought that if I was\Ngoing somewhere, we could go together.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.62,0:15:34.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.16,0:15:37.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, let's go, Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.04,0:15:47.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come right on in.\NWelcome to our establishment.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.84,0:15:50.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We have two menus prepared for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.17,0:15:52.26,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Gray Course\NRosy Course
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.84,0:15:52.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which one would you like?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.20,0:16:13.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I recommend this course.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.11,0:16:17.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Today's problems might end up\Ncosting you surprisingly dearly.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.37,0:16:18.12,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Rosy Course
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.95,0:16:19.45,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Rosy Course
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.50,0:16:21.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}...?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.08,0:16:27.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ugh, all right. Today's gym class\Ngot washed out due to rain,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.42,0:16:29.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so I still have some\Ndiscretionary energy left.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.26,0:16:30.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.38,0:16:34.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just how limited is your energy, anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.76,0:16:36.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Leave me alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.14,0:16:37.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.10,0:16:38.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.26,0:16:39.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold up.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.56,0:16:42.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going, too. I'm a little curious.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.77,0:16:45.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fuku-{\i1}chan{\i0}, would you cover\Nmy desk for a bit?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.48,0:16:45.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.23,0:16:49.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After all, I can't just abandon\Nmy library duties, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.61,0:16:50.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See you, Satoshi.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.86,0:16:53.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold down the fort here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.78,0:16:57.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So then, Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}, where are we going?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.70,0:16:59.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The art room.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.03,0:17:00.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the building across the way?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.54,0:17:04.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yep, far away. That's why\NI didn't want to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.08,0:17:06.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You really are lazy, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.67,0:17:07.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's over there?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.21,0:17:09.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First, let's set things straight.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.88,0:17:12.01,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Lunch Break
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.88,0:17:12.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As far as how the book is being used,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.01,0:17:15.05,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,After School
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.01,0:17:16.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,there aren't any girls using anything\Nthat huge during their breaks.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.05,0:17:16.22,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,No\NNo\NNo
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.26,0:17:20.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means the only conceivable\Nuse would be during class time.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.80,0:17:24.31,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Class
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.01,0:17:22.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are the only classes that have\Nstudents from the same year,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.77,0:17:24.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but taken from different homerooms?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.60,0:17:27.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gym and fine arts subjects, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.98,0:17:27.06,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Gym\NMusic\NArt\NCalligraphy
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.06,0:17:32.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right. Each week before class, those five\Ntook turns coming to borrow the book.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.19,0:17:35.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't get why they would do it each week.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.90,0:17:37.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The checkout period lasts for two weeks.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.99,0:17:39.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With a book that big,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.53,0:17:42.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it would be easier returning it each week\Nthan lugging it around, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.58,0:17:43.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, that's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.04,0:17:47.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.17,0:17:49.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the same smell as the book.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.21,0:17:50.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.42,0:17:51.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look inside and see for yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.59,0:17:57.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what the book is being used for.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.93,0:18:04.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The 2nd-year D, E, and F combined classes\Npainted pictures for their art class.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.48,0:18:07.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The book's binding makes it\Na perfect motif for a painting.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.44,0:18:10.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was the smell of paint.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.27,0:18:13.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How did you figure it out?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.78,0:18:14.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How did I...?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.66,0:18:20.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just a stroke of inspiration.\NI simply got lucky.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.37,0:18:24.50,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Library
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.20,0:18:25.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, nicely done, nicely done!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.46,0:18:30.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I never would have imagined\Nusing it as a motif in a painting.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.67,0:18:34.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How did you ever figure that out?\NOreki, you're weird.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.38,0:18:38.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?\NThere's nobody more average than I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.18,0:18:40.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I don't know about {\i1}that{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.34,0:18:44.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Still, you really did\Nsurprise me, Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.01,0:18:47.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm interested in what goes on\Ninside that head of yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.10,0:18:47.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're interested?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.94,0:18:48.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.85,0:18:52.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd even like to crack it open\Nand look around inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.82,0:18:56.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not that fancy a brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.15,0:18:58.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's nothing for an honor student\Nlike you to gain by looking at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.15,0:19:01.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah? You're an honor student?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.87,0:19:04.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. We haven't\Nhad our midterms yet,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.70,0:19:07.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but I'm sure her grades will be\Nat the top of the class for our year.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.66,0:19:11.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no. No matter how good a grade I get,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.50,0:19:14.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it's nothing more than\Nputting all the parts together.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.42,0:19:19.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not the individual parts, but how his\Nsystem of thought develops that I want to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.18,0:19:21.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh-huh...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.51,0:19:22.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For that matter,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.93,0:19:27.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it's her sense of smell that remains\Na far greater mystery to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.43,0:19:30.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Knowing Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}, it's\Njust possible that...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.52,0:19:31.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.15,0:19:33.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, nothing. Never mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.40,0:19:38.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, in any event, I had a\Nfairly entertaining time of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.36,0:19:39.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What about you, Chitanda-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.57,0:19:43.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course I had fun!\NThe time seemed to fly by.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.70,0:19:48.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I spent hours on it, and still\Ndidn't get it. It's so frustrating!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.25,0:19:52.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't I tell you he could\Ncome in handy once in a while?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.08,0:19:54.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I just can't accept\Nbeing outdone by Oreki!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.88,0:19:56.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It really is frustrating!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.30,0:19:58.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, now, Mayaka, take it easy!\NSomething's off.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.63,0:20:00.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Something is off here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.55,0:20:04.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't ever be like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.22,0:20:08.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's off here? What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.27,0:20:10.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I know what you mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.98,0:20:13.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once in a long while,\Nthere's a flash of light,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.85,0:20:16.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and in an instant...\NOreki-{\i1}san{\i0}, you can't leave!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.02,0:20:18.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why not? Oh, the anthologies.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.90,0:20:21.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. We have to\Nwait for the librarian.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.53,0:20:23.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sometimes Hotaro does\Ngo out to lunch, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.07,0:20:26.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Sometimes{\i0}? Are you sure you\Naren't overestimating that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.95,0:20:28.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmph.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.04,0:20:31.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ibara-{\i1}san{\i0}, thank you. You can leave now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.83,0:20:35.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right. You are back, Itoigawa-{\i1}sensei{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.21,0:20:38.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sensei, I am Fukube Satoshi,\Nfrom the Classic Lit Club.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.84,0:20:41.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We are looking for back-number issues,\Nso we can make our own anthology.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.26,0:20:43.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Would it be okay if we checked the stacks?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.34,0:20:47.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Classic Lit Club? Anthologies?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.64,0:20:49.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're in the Classic Lit Club?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.81,0:20:55.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, unfortunately, the anthology\Nback-numbers aren't in the stacks.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.90,0:20:57.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure they haven't been overlooked?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.11,0:21:03.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If they were there, I'd remember.\NWell, if you'll excuse me...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.11,0:21:05.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh... Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.00,0:21:12.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There you have it, Chitanda-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.12,0:21:15.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This {\i1}is {\i0}a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.17,0:21:16.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll find them soon enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.50,0:21:23.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you say, Oreki?\NWas it refreshing to solve that problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.22,0:21:24.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not especially.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.26,0:21:25.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, really?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.55,0:21:27.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess that's that. Let's go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.30,0:21:30.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I did glean something today, and all.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.51,0:21:32.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.10,0:21:34.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing. It's a personal matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.18,0:21:35.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that again?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.52,0:21:41.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, knowing Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0},\Nit's just possible...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.58,0:21:51.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Oreki residence.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.45,0:21:53.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello? I-It's Chitanda.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.42,0:21:57.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chitanda?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.67,0:22:01.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, I'm sorry. You weren't\Nsleeping, were you?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.25,0:22:05.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you know. I thought you\Nwere my sister calling.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.05,0:22:09.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, what are you calling for on a Sunday?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.14,0:22:15.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you'll forgive me, I'd like\Nto see you today, if possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.02,0:22:17.02,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Pineapple Sand
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.02,0:22:18.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is something I\Nearnestly need to speak to you about.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.20,0:22:31.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's taking her time.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.13,0:22:48.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,P-Please excuse me for\Nbringing you out here.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.93,0:22:51.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.07,0:23:10.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, was there something you wanted?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.57,0:23:11.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.41,0:23:14.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm asking you why you asked me\Nout to this coffee shop.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.12,0:23:21.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're the one who suggested\Nthis place, Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.46,0:23:23.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm out of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.09,0:23:25.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? P-Please wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.34,0:23:29.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's my precious Sunday! I can't squander\Nit playing along with one of your bits!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.68,0:23:31.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.89,0:23:35.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just nervous.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.43,0:23:39.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nervous, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.56,0:23:45.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you planning to confess\Nyour love to me, or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.61,0:23:54.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There may be {\i1}something\N{\i0}I have to confess, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.33,0:23:56.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.09,0:24:08.01,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Tonight it turns to love{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.01,0:24:11.76,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Meet me in a pleasant dream{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.76,0:24:15.76,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Make sure that you find me, okay?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.76,0:24:21.14,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Our snooze-time date{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.24,0:24:41.33,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The heat of your budding warmth troubles me{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.08,0:24:52.13,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Don't you understand how I feel yet?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.51,0:24:59.01,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}There isn't supposed to be\Nany significance in your glance{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.01,0:25:04.44,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I mean, it's the same one\Nyou give all your friends{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.44,0:25:10.11,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The tiny wishing star fading\Ninto the morning light{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.11,0:25:15.16,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and the magic it works during the night\N(I wish you would notice){\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.16,0:25:18.16,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Tonight it turns to love{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.16,0:25:21.87,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Meet me in a pleasant dream{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.87,0:25:25.92,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Make sure that you find me, okay?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.92,0:25:31.17,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Our snooze-time date{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.14,0:25:43.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, "The Circumstances\Nof the Classic Lit Club's Scion."
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.39,0:25:43.22,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,The Circumstances of the Classic Lit Club's Scion
